
An Enum is a unique type of data type in java which is generally a collection (set) of constants. 
More specifically, a Java Enum type is a unique kind of Java class. 
An Enum can hold constants, methods, etc. An Enum keyword can be used with if statement, switch statement, and iteration, etc
// Java Program to show working of Enum
// Keyword when declared outside the Class
enum Days {
	MONDAY,
	TUESDAY,
	WEDNESDAY,
	THURSDAY,
	FRIDAY,
	SATURDAY,
	SUNDAY;
}

public class temp {

	// Driver method
	public static void main(String[] args)
	{
		Days x = Days.FRIDAY;
		System.out.println(x);
	}
}
